google trend

Functions

gtrends function retrieves a list of dataframe which related to Google Trends.

res <- gtrends(c("Messi", "Ronaldo"))
plot(res)

You can select trends in specific region, such as countries. The below graph shows trend in United Kingdom to set geo augument GB.

res2 <- gtrends(c("Messi", "Ronaldo"), geo = c("GB"))
plot(res2)

You can also select specific categories. In the following example, Sports categories, 20, are selected.

res3 <- gtrends(c("Messi", "Ronaldo"), category  = 20)
plot(res3)

queries<-res$related_queries

queries2 <- queries %>%
  filter(keyword == "Messi") %>%
  mutate(value = stringr::str_replace(value, "messi","") )%>%
  mutate(value = stringr::str_trim(value)) %>%
  select(-keyword, -category)

queries2 %>%
  gt() %>%
  tab_header(
    title = "Query Keyword with Messi, Google Trend"
  )
